    <title>About predictors</title>
    <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160922T160546+0200" comment="Copied from Launchpad: https://blueprints.launchpad.net/dhis2/+spec/predictors"?>
    <para>Predictors are data elements automatically generated from samples of current and past
        data. You use predictors to analyse previous data in order to predict future values, for
        example for disease surveillance.</para>
    <para>A predictor specifies an expression and a set of *sample constraints* (identical to the
        current implementation of validation rules). This includes a period type, organisation unit
        levels, and parameters specifying past or periodic sample windows.</para>
    <?oxy_comment_end?>
